4) Recommended next steps for you (to get a compilation result)
Option A — Run the GitHub Action (recommended if you want CI logs):
- Set GH_TOKEN in the repository secrets or the environment the action uses, then run the workflow (workflow_dispatch) in GitHub. The workflow run will produce full javac diagnostics if there are compilation errors:
  - Inputs: branch=main (or desired branch), build_type=compile-only
- Or trigger the workflow via the GitHub UI -> Actions -> Build Application -> Run workflow.

Option B — Run locally to see compilation errors immediately:
- On a machine with JDK 21 installed (or use the Gradle wrapper's toolchain), from the repo root run:
  - chmod +x ./gradlew
  - ./gradlew clean compileJava --continue --console=plain -i
- The above will run the same compile step and print all javac errors. Use Java 21 (the workflow uses Temurin 21).

